==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Rubiaceous
<hw>Ru`bi*a"ceous</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>rubia</ets> madder, fr. <ets>rubeus</ets> red.]</ety>
<fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>Of or pertaining to a very large natural order of
plants (<spn>Rubiaceae</spn>) named after the madder (<spn>Rubia
tinctoria</spn>), and including about three hundred and seventy genera
and over four thousand species. Among them are the coffee tree, the
trees yielding peruvian bark and quinine, the madder, the quaker ladies,
and the trees bearing the edible fruits called genipap and Sierre Leone
peach, besides many plants noted for the beauty or the fragrance of
their blossoms.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Rubiacin</ent>⟦br⟧
